description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Therapy Support Worker - Stroke and Neurology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2/3 depending on experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time – 34 hours (per week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated and reliable Occupational Therapy Technical Instructor/ Occupational Therapy Assistant to work in our Stroke and Neurology Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work alongside, and under the supervision of the Occupational Therapists in providing individual and structured assessment and intervention for Stroke and Neurology patients. This will predominantly involve assessment on the ward, but will occasionally also involve assessment in the patients’ own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A high level of inter-professional working exists on the Stroke Unit benefiting the patients and all members of the MDT. The Trust has a 13 bed Acute Stroke Unit, with additional beds allocated to other Neurology patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include assisting the occupational therapy team to complete rehabilitation sessions to support patients’ recovery, as well as supporting preparations for discharge home. There will also be opportunities to support group work, alongside a qualified therapist, and some admin responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible and adaptable approach is required to meet the needs of the service. NHS experience would be an advantage but is not essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post may require some weekend/bank holiday working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will demonstrate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective prioritisation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work as part of a team and alone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mature clinical reasoning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean driving license and use of car is essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for professional and personal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-service training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical supervision and Appraisal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly and supportive working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Peer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated CPD time and a firm commitment to learning and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Surrey NHS Foundation Trust is a leading General Hospital and specialist tertiary centre for cancer, Oral and Maxillo-facial surgery and pathology. The hospital serves a population of 320,000 for emergency and general hospital services and is the lead specialist centre for cancer patients in Surrey, West Sussex and Hampshire, serving a population of 1.2 million.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our annual income is £199 million and we have 527 beds and 14 operating theatres. We employ 2,800 staff, making us the second largest employer in Guildford. We have very close links with the University of Surrey and have an extensive education, training and research portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 05/10/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For further information, an informal visit/chat please contact Suzanne Ward on 01483 571122 ext 4766 or 4679&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;e-mail: &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;suzanne.ward@ nhs.net&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;victoria.macdonald@ nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
